# =============================================================================
# .clinerules - Schema Directory Standards
# JSON Schema & Data Contract Governance
# =============================================================================
# This file defines rules for maintaining JSON schemas and data contracts
# to ensure consistency with LaTeX specifications and implementation code.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DIRECTORY OVERVIEW
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Purpose
This directory contains all JSON schemas and YAML data contracts for the 
enterprise AI platform. Schemas serve as:
- **Data Contracts**: Define the structure of data exchanged between services
- **Validation Rules**: Enforce data integrity at runtime
- **Documentation**: Machine-readable specification of data structures

## Directory Structure

| Subdirectory | Description | Related Spec |
|--------------|-------------|--------------|
| `arabic/` | Arabic AP Invoice Processing schemas | docs/latex/specs/arabic/ |
| `common/` | Shared enums, types, and base schemas | All specs |
| `regulations/` | AI governance and compliance schemas | docs/latex/specs/regulations/ |
| `simula/` | Training data framework schemas | docs/latex/specs/simula/ |
| `tb/` | Trial Balance review schemas | docs/latex/specs/tb/ |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SCHEMA STANDARDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Required Schema Metadata

Every JSON schema MUST include:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://sap-oss.example.com/schemas/<domain>/<name>.schema.json",
  "title": "Human-Readable Title",
  "description": "What this schema defines and its purpose",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["field1", "field2"],
  "additionalProperties": false
}
```

## Field Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Identifiers | Suffix with `_id` | `persona_id`, `resource_id` |
| Timestamps | Suffix with `_at` or `_timestamp` | `created_at`, `audit_timestamp` |
| Flags | Prefix with `is_` or `has_` | `is_active`, `has_attachment` |
| Counts | Suffix with `_count` | `line_item_count` |
| Audit fields | Prefix with `audit_` | `audit_id`, `audit_trail` |

## Schema File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Entity schema | `<entity>.schema.json` | `variance-record.schema.json` |
| Entry schema | `<entity>-entry.schema.json` | `audit-trail-entry.schema.json` |
| Extract schema | `<entity>-extract.schema.json` | `tb-extract.schema.json` |
| Params schema | `<entity>-params.schema.json` | `entity-params.schema.json` |
| YAML configs | `<name>.yaml` | `risk-register.yaml` |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPEC-DRIFT PREVENTION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Schema-Spec Synchronization Rules

1. **Schema changes require spec updates**
   - Adding/removing fields → Update corresponding LaTeX chapter
   - Changing field types → Update data model documentation
   - Modifying enums → Update enum tables in spec

2. **Spec changes require schema updates**
   - New data structures in spec → Create corresponding schema
   - Modified field descriptions → Update schema description
   - Changed validation rules → Update schema constraints

## Related Files

When modifying schemas, check these related files:
- `docs/schema/spec-code-mapping.yaml` - Update artifact mappings
- `docs/schema/registry.json` - Update schema registry
- `docs/latex/specs/<domain>/` - Update corresponding spec chapters

## Drift Detection Commands

```bash
# Check for drift in this directory
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=<domain>

# Validate all schemas are valid JSON/YAML
make audit-check-mapping

# View current drift exceptions
make audit-exceptions-review
```

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SHARED ENUMS GOVERNANCE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Shared Enums (common/enums.yaml)

The following enums are shared across multiple specs and MUST be referenced
from `common/enums.yaml` rather than redefined locally:

| Enum | Consumers | RFC Required for Changes |
|------|-----------|--------------------------|
| `risk_status` | TB, BSS | Yes |
| `decision_outcome` | TB, Arabic, Regulations | Yes |
| `variance_type` | TB | Yes |
| `workflow_state_type` | TB, BSS | Yes |
| `audit_action` | TB, BSS, Arabic | Yes |
| `source_system` | TB, Arabic | Yes |

## Adding/Modifying Shared Enums

1. Submit RFC to Controls Architecture Team
2. 5-day review period required
3. All consuming spec owners must approve
4. One-release deprecation window for breaking changes
5. Update all related specs in same PR

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VALIDATION REQUIREMENTS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Schema Validation

All schemas must pass:
1. **JSON Schema validity** - Valid JSON Schema Draft 2020-12
2. **YAML validity** - Valid YAML 1.2 (for YAML files)
3. **Reference resolution** - All $ref pointers resolve
4. **Example validation** - All examples validate against schema

## Running Validation

```bash
# Validate all schemas
python3 docs/schema/validate.py

# Validate specific schema
python3 docs/schema/validate.py --schema simula/taxonomy.schema.json
```

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHANGE WORKFLOW
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Before Making Changes

1. Check spec-code mapping: `make audit-check-mapping`
2. Identify related specs: See `spec-code-mapping.yaml`
3. Run drift audit: `make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=<domain>`

## After Making Changes

1. Update related LaTeX spec chapters
2. Update schema registry (`registry.json`)
3. Run validation: `python3 docs/schema/validate.py`
4. Run drift audit: `make audit-spec-drift`
5. Update CHANGELOG.md with changes

